Although it is generally not possible in Germany to retroactively assign a USt-IdNr. to a tax subject, the responsible person in charge of the German tax administration did so retroactively on 1 May 2004.
The German CLO retroactively assigns a USt-IdNr. if the German entrepreneur has not caused the delayed allocation; for example, if the CLO caused the delay after the application of the taxable person for the grant of a USt-IdNr..
In this case, the CLO grants the USt-IdNr. retroactively, because according to § 6 UStG the entrepreneur does not need a valid USt-IdNr. for an intra-Community delivery.
Conversely, a German acquirer does not need the (valid) USt-IdNr. of its supplier to declare the intra-Community acquisition.
Because of these procedural differences between the Member States, the German CLO granted retroactive authorisation in this particular case.
